## 2026-04-23 — Liminal reader mobile (horizontal half-pages)
- **Prior:** Mobile used the same horizontal slide animation as desktop, shrinking spreads and making text hard to read.
- **Now:** At `max-width: 640px`, the reader becomes a **horizontal scroll-snap** track. The cover is shown as a contained single page; every following asset is rendered as **two snap pages** (left half then right half) using `background-size: 200%` + `background-position: 0%/100%` so the split is a true 50/50 vertical cut. Progress/keyboard/swipe/thumbnail navigation map to the new logical page indices; resizing rebuilds layout and preserves the current file.
